                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm starting this thread to hopefully have a nice discussion (no bnet flamers) involving peoples views of what constitutes proper PvP etiquette.  A.K.A. what is and what is not ganking?
<br />

<br />
Is it ganking if you are the same level as your target but you attack them while they are fighting a mob?
<br />

<br />
In another thread a poster talks about that very kind of battle yet another poster seems to think this is ganking and is "unethical" PvP.   If the word ethics can even be used to describe PvP.
<br />

<br />
Anyways, maybe we can help the people who are new to PvP (of which there are a lot in WoW it seems) to understand what's going on better.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />WoW > EQ
<br />
WoW > EQ2
<br />
Blizzard > SOE
<br />
/flip</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
