                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I do not and will not go to a lower level area for the express purpose of killing newbs
<br />

<br />
I do not corpse camp
<br />

<br />
I do not kill someone that is AFK
<br />

<br />
I will kill anyone that I can, regardless of level if I see them in a contested area,,,,  in other words, if I see a level 8 running thru a level 20+ contested zone, I don't have a problem with killing him.  He's got to know and think that if he's in a contested zone, I'm an enemy much like a kos mob. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  (not sure if I'm making sense here....)
<br />

<br />
Now that's not to say I kill everyone I see (kill or be killed that is), mostly it depends on what I'm doing, if I'm in a hurry, if I'm feeling aggressive or if they attack first and last but not least, if it's a person I recognize as someone who readily engages in pvp while in contested zones.
<br />

<br />
Also, due to the way mobs are leashed, I don't have a problem engaging in PVP while a person is on a mob.   I'm not on a server where I "request to duel"  and therefore wait for the other to get full health and full buffs.  I'm on a pvp server.  At the same time, I fully expect that people will attack my group and I while we're engaged with a mob (or me solo).....  and it's happened, more times than I've ever attacked someone else <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
It's PVP for a reason, and for me, part of that fun of it is knowing that I have to constantly be aware of my surroundings, what I'm doing, where I'm going, etc</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
