                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is my perspective as a non-PvPer, so take it with a grain of salt if you will.
<br />

<br />
Ganking, or even call it dishonorable conduct, would include:
<br />

<br />
Attacking a player who is already engaged in combat, be it PvE or PvP.
<br />

<br />
Attacking a player who has little to no chance of defending themselves or killing you (i.e. a level 30 attacking a level 8 )
<br />

<br />
Corpse camping.
<br />

<br />
Many-on-one combat, where the outcome is certain that the 'one' *is* going to die - even if one or more of the 'many' will die.
<br />

<br />
If, on the other hand, the outcome is dependant on skill, that the match is fairly even (I know that some classes will always be able to beat another class of the same or similar level - too bad for the loser) then I don't feel it would be ganking.
<br />

<br />
Griefing would be any conduct designed to ruin someone's play experience, repeated ganking, if you will.
<br />

<br />
And yes, I differenciate between the two.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Max
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=368646" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fanamax the Enchanter</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
