                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have a hard time seeing corpse camping as griefing.  In EQ corpse camping was a lot worse in that you had to actually run to the corpse and loot it.  In WoW you can rez within a certain range and depending on the local terrain you stand a good chance of being able to rez in secret.
<br />

<br />
I've noticed that a lot of people seem to feel that rogues engaging in the kind of combat (assasination)  that they are designed for are considered griefers.   Rogues aren't duelers in that fair fights aren't what we look for.  We exploit opportunities.  It just seems that many would consider that griefing and in some cases I tend to agree.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />WoW > EQ
