                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My opinion only of course.
<br />

<br />
Ganking is:
<br />
Corpse Camping as defined as killing someone, sitting at or near their corpse till they return for the express purpose of killing them again when they rez themselves.  
<br />

<br />
Going into a much lower level area with no other purpose in mind but to kill lower level people because "You Can"
<br />

<br />
What is not Ganking...
<br />
Killing someone lower level traveling thru a higher level zone.  
<br />
A group of lower levels, say for example 3 lvl 20's taking on 1 lvl 40.  This is not ganking, it is fair play.  Especially since the lvl 40 is perfectly correct in gathering 2 or 3 of his friends and returning the favor on the lower levels if appropriate.
<br />

<br />
And what is most certainly not ganking is killing any idiot who engages you in combat first, regardless of how far below you in level they are.
<br />

<br />
As to killing someone who is engaged with a mob and killing them...I don't belive it is ganking, but I don't think it is an honorable kill either.  If you are without honor have at it.  It's part of the game mechanics and th ere is nothing that says you can not use the enviornment to your advantage, which is what you would be doing in that case.
<br />

<br />
Rogue's are perfectly correct in assasination type attacks and I say that as a non-rogue.  It's a skill given to you.  Use it.  Be aware that on my hunter I will be using my find invisible tracking ability and may just turn the tables......all in the name of the game and fun of course.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Mistofelees MagikCat
<br />
67 Enchanter &lt;Retired&gt;
<br />
