<br />
Yes - and no.
<br />

<br />
Going after the same camp of mob_01 and named_mob_02?  Certainly.
<br />

<br />
Kill 7 of roaming_beast_mob_03 - easily soloable.  Well, certainly you can initiate PvP anytime you want to in a contested zone.  But, do you want to spend your time ganking and being ganked in return (with no reward no matter how successful you - except perhaps notoriety amongst those you killed who will not hesitate to return the favor)?  Or do you want to quest, xp, and level?
<br />

<br />
For me it's an easy choice.  Doesn't mean I'm any less committed to PvP, I chose a PvP server after all.  I'll also say there's nothing wrong with ganking.  If your motto is "kill all opposing faction on sight", great.  You're entitled to do what you want.
<br />

<br />
