                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I started EverQuest, I was on Vallon Zek because that was where my friends were.  Eventually I moved and they followed me.  The funny thing is that what finally made me move is that I lost my illusions when somebody attacked me in PvP, effectively removing my ability as an Enchanter to do business in enemy cities (with NPCs, I mean).  That's kind of a silly thing to be a last-straw, but it was.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes I do miss the added thrill though of wondering if that group of enemy players is going to walk by or attack me.  Also, the thrill of having my AE spells agro my group mate's pets on to me, and having to kill their pets because they were too dumb to pull them off (probably AFK).  But then with the faction system in WoW that shouldn't happen <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ceilon and Hawafena
<br />
Night Elf Hunter and Pretty Green Spider
<br />
Argent Dawn (East Coast RP)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
